WEBVTT

00:06.130 --> 00:07.047
MONTROSE FREEMAN:
You wanna run chest first

00:07.130 --> 00:08.547
into some magical treasure hunt.

00:09.130 --> 00:10.798
We already got one large
gun ambush.

00:10.881 --> 00:12.005
You won't tell them nothing,
boy.

00:12.089 --> 00:13.589
How you know
there's 34 lodges?

00:14.381 --> 00:16.506
LETI LEWIS: You really gonna
let him chase his tale,

00:16.589 --> 00:18.547
looking for answers you already
have?

00:20.339 --> 00:22.297
ATTICUS FREEMAN:
Leti's inheritance
didn't come from her mother.

00:22.547 --> 00:23.589
It came from you.

00:24.964 --> 00:26.422
So, you want something
in this house?

00:26.506 --> 00:28.214
I just want Hiram's orrery.

00:28.297 --> 00:29.339
(TIRES SCREECHING)

00:29.673 --> 00:31.673
LETI: The police captain was
asking all these questions about

00:31.756 --> 00:34.214
the Winthrop Palace, like he had
some sorta connection to it.

00:34.756 --> 00:37.756
You come here and try and take
my lodge's rightful property.

00:38.005 --> 00:40.589
Forgive me. Did I miss
your official initiation

00:40.673 --> 00:41.547
into the order?

00:41.923 --> 00:45.047
WOMAN: Titus locked his pages
in a booby-trap vault.

00:45.255 --> 00:48.339
Imagine the possibilities
if the pages were to be found?

00:50.422 --> 00:51.297
I'm sorry.

00:52.297 --> 00:55.339
HIPPOLYTA FREEMAN:
For us, it's a rat race
to the finish line.

00:55.547 --> 00:56.631
And it's winner takes it all.

00:56.964 --> 00:59.339
What if I told you that
I could change your life,

00:59.422 --> 01:00.464
forever?

01:01.464 --> 01:02.631
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:03.673 --> 01:05.714
[TV static drones]

01:05.798 --> 01:08.047
[bright tone]

01:08.130 --> 01:11.130
[birds chirping]

01:19.798 --> 01:22.798
- [grunting]

01:24.172 --> 01:26.631
[groans]

01:37.464 --> 01:40.297
[ominous music]

01:40.381 --> 01:47.339
♪ ♪

01:50.005 --> 01:52.923
[grunting]

01:53.005 --> 02:00.005
♪ ♪

02:07.172 --> 02:09.464
Wake up, Ruby.

02:11.714 --> 02:13.297
Wake up.

02:13.381 --> 02:16.339
[eerie music]

02:16.422 --> 02:23.381
♪ ♪

02:25.506 --> 02:28.214
[breathing heavily]

02:32.714 --> 02:34.089
[grunts]

02:40.547 --> 02:41.506
[moans]

02:41.589 --> 02:43.506
[gasps]

02:43.589 --> 02:45.923
[bell dings]

02:46.005 --> 02:48.464
- You lost, ma'am?

02:48.547 --> 02:50.798
- I'm Ruby Baptiste.

02:50.881 --> 02:53.130
I'm...

02:53.214 --> 02:54.506
[panting]

02:54.589 --> 02:56.214
Stop staring at me!

02:56.297 --> 02:58.297
[grunts]
- Ma'am, you okay?

02:58.381 --> 03:00.881
[siren wailing]

03:00.964 --> 03:02.589
[tense music]

03:02.673 --> 03:03.964
- What did you do to her, boy?

03:04.047 --> 03:05.255
- I was just trying to help.

03:05.339 --> 03:06.673
- [growls]

03:06.756 --> 03:07.714
- It's okay, ma'am.

03:07.798 --> 03:08.839
He can't hurt you anymore.

03:08.923 --> 03:11.339
You're safe now.
- Get over there.

03:11.422 --> 03:12.673
- [grunting]

03:12.756 --> 03:14.839
- Did you molest her?
Huh?

03:14.923 --> 03:16.631
Answer me, boy!

03:16.714 --> 03:20.172
What did you do to her?
- Wait, officer!

03:20.255 --> 03:21.714
He didn't hurt me.

03:21.798 --> 03:23.047
I just--I got lost.

03:23.130 --> 03:25.547
- There's no need to protect
this animal, ma'am.

03:25.631 --> 03:26.673
If he did something to you--

03:26.756 --> 03:28.047
- I swear he didn't.

03:28.130 --> 03:30.172
He was just trying to help me.

03:30.255 --> 03:34.881
♪ ♪

03:35.005 --> 03:36.881
- Let's get you
somewhere safe, ma'am.

03:36.964 --> 03:39.172
Okay?

03:39.255 --> 03:40.255
[whispering]
You're all right.

03:40.339 --> 03:42.089
- What's happening over there?

03:42.172 --> 03:44.130
- You see that woman?

03:45.839 --> 03:48.214
- Right in here.
Mm-hmm.

03:48.297 --> 03:50.589
Mm-hmm.

03:50.673 --> 03:53.881
[radio tuning]

03:53.964 --> 03:58.255
- ♪ Somebody new,
but tonight ♪

03:58.339 --> 04:00.714
- Your husband's been
real worried about you, ma'am.

04:00.798 --> 04:03.881
- ♪ You belong to me ♪

04:03.964 --> 04:06.089
- [grunting]

04:06.172 --> 04:07.881
Mm-mm.

04:07.964 --> 04:09.381
No.

04:09.464 --> 04:10.673
You can't take me back there.

04:10.756 --> 04:12.047
- It's okay, ma'am.
- You don't understand.

04:12.130 --> 04:14.881
He's not my husband.
He did something to me.

04:14.964 --> 04:17.255
- And he told the operator
all about your condition.

04:17.339 --> 04:18.964
You just need your pills.

04:19.047 --> 04:21.172
- [grunting]

04:21.255 --> 04:22.130
Let me out of here.

04:22.214 --> 04:24.089
[bones cracking, groaning]

04:24.172 --> 04:27.422
- ♪ Way down by the stream ♪

04:27.506 --> 04:28.923
- [gasps]
- Holy shit.

04:29.005 --> 04:31.923
I think these are the fits
her husband mentioned.

04:32.005 --> 04:32.923
- [gasping]

04:33.005 --> 04:35.422
- ♪ In the silvery moonlight ♪

04:35.506 --> 04:36.422
- [gasps]

04:36.506 --> 04:39.464
- ♪ My honey, I know ♪
- ♪ I know ♪

04:39.547 --> 04:41.631
both: ♪ With the dawn ♪

04:41.714 --> 04:43.964
♪ That you ♪

04:44.047 --> 04:46.130
♪ Will be gone ♪

04:46.214 --> 04:48.589
♪ But tonight ♪

04:48.673 --> 04:51.589
♪ You belong to me ♪

04:51.673 --> 04:55.422
♪ Just to little old me ♪

04:55.506 --> 04:58.464
- [groaning]

04:58.547 --> 05:01.464
[ominous music]

05:01.547 --> 05:03.506
♪ ♪

05:03.589 --> 05:04.798
- Oh.

05:04.881 --> 05:06.089
Stop fighting it.

05:06.172 --> 05:07.130
- [gasping]

05:07.214 --> 05:09.798
- You're only slowing
the process.

05:09.881 --> 05:11.673
[bones cracking]
- [gasping]

05:11.756 --> 05:14.130
[crying out]

05:14.214 --> 05:15.631
- Pickets and non-strikers...

05:15.714 --> 05:18.214
- Wouldn't want to disturb
the neighbors.

05:18.297 --> 05:20.422
- Cermak Road
and Cicero Avenue.

05:20.506 --> 05:21.422
Cicero...

05:21.506 --> 05:25.130
- [grunting]

05:25.214 --> 05:28.172
[screaming]

05:28.255 --> 05:31.255
[gasping]

05:33.547 --> 05:36.506
[screaming]

05:36.589 --> 05:43.464
♪ ♪

05:45.673 --> 05:48.839
- [sighs]

05:48.923 --> 05:51.464
- I don't want--
[panting]

05:51.547 --> 05:53.714
[straining]
I don't want to die.

05:53.798 --> 05:56.297
[gasping]

05:56.381 --> 05:58.881
- He would say
that metamorphosis isn't death.

05:58.964 --> 06:00.297
- [gasping]

06:00.381 --> 06:03.506
- American-born Greek soprano
Maria Callas

06:03.589 --> 06:06.005
christened the stage
in Italian opera "Norma."

06:06.089 --> 06:09.089
- [grunting]

06:10.547 --> 06:14.172
- [grunts]

06:14.255 --> 06:17.381
- Breaking news: a swarm
of 16 billion Kenyan locusts

06:17.464 --> 06:19.214
are moving
across North Africa,

06:19.297 --> 06:20.964
with Great Britain
in their crosshairs.

06:21.047 --> 06:23.381
Scientists say locust nymphs
hatch from eggs,

06:23.464 --> 06:25.547
and they will go through
five molting stages

06:25.631 --> 06:26.923
where they will shed
their skin

06:27.005 --> 06:28.339
and develop their wings.

06:28.422 --> 06:29.506
After seven days,
they will reach

06:29.589 --> 06:32.422
full sexual maturity
as adult locusts,

06:32.506 --> 06:35.756
destined to devour
everything in their path.

06:35.839 --> 06:37.798
[birds chirping]

06:37.881 --> 06:40.839
[children shouting]

06:42.047 --> 06:46.547
[elevator clunking,
elevator dings]

06:46.631 --> 06:48.547
- I'll go by the library
and get some children's books.

06:48.631 --> 06:49.881
- See if you can teach her
enough English

06:49.964 --> 06:51.214
to write up a protection spell.

06:51.297 --> 06:52.714
Good idea.

06:52.798 --> 06:53.673
[door squeaks]

06:53.756 --> 06:57.089
- Right?
Think so.

06:57.172 --> 06:59.381
- Hey, Pop.
What you doing here?

06:59.464 --> 07:02.089
- Where's Yahima?

07:02.172 --> 07:04.130
- Gone.

07:04.214 --> 07:05.255
- What?

07:05.339 --> 07:07.089
You just let her
walk out of here?

07:07.172 --> 07:09.255
[foreboding music]

07:09.339 --> 07:12.923
How long ago?
Maybe we can find her.

07:13.005 --> 07:14.089
- Titus's pages?

07:14.172 --> 07:21.172
♪ ♪

07:24.631 --> 07:27.089
[grunting]
- [gasps]

07:27.172 --> 07:28.255
Atticus!

07:28.339 --> 07:29.589
Atticus!

07:29.673 --> 07:31.631
Atticus, stop!

07:31.714 --> 07:33.130
Somebody, help!

07:33.214 --> 07:35.214
Somebody!
He's gonna kill him!

07:35.297 --> 07:37.589
- Whoa, whoa, hey, hey, hey!

07:37.673 --> 07:39.422
- [grunting]

07:39.506 --> 07:41.673
Get the fuck off me!

07:44.130 --> 07:45.089
- Montrose!

07:45.172 --> 07:47.964
Montrose.
Montrose, come on.

07:48.047 --> 07:49.130
Go get some ice!

07:49.214 --> 07:52.130
[frantic music]

07:52.214 --> 07:55.130
♪ ♪

07:55.214 --> 07:56.506
- Did you take photos of 'em?

07:56.589 --> 07:58.005
- Of what?
- Titus's pages!

07:58.089 --> 07:59.756
- Tic, I need you to calm down.

07:59.839 --> 08:01.172
- God damn it, Leti!

08:01.255 --> 08:03.464
If you took photos of 'em,
give 'em to me!

08:03.547 --> 08:07.214
- [breathing heavily]

08:22.422 --> 08:23.714
[door slams]

08:33.422 --> 08:36.381
- A butterfly lives a full life
before it dies.

08:37.631 --> 08:40.130
And a caterpillar emerges
from the same cells,

08:40.214 --> 08:42.839
the essence of the butterfly,

08:42.923 --> 08:45.339
yet different.

08:45.422 --> 08:47.506
It's more.

08:47.589 --> 08:50.547
I wanted to apply this process

08:50.631 --> 08:53.255
of metamorphosis to humans.

08:57.255 --> 09:01.172
But my research was
all theoretical.

09:01.255 --> 09:04.631
It was laughed at
by the academic community.

09:06.714 --> 09:10.589
Until, by chance,

09:10.673 --> 09:14.547
I met a disgraced professor

09:14.631 --> 09:17.464
named Hiram Epstein.

09:19.964 --> 09:21.255
He wanted nothing more

09:21.339 --> 09:25.172
than to understand
the universe,

09:25.255 --> 09:28.381
but it was beyond his reach.

09:28.464 --> 09:31.214
So he created doorways.

09:31.297 --> 09:32.839
Not scientific, mind you,

09:32.923 --> 09:35.964
but magical.

09:36.047 --> 09:39.214
Though one could argue
they're one and the same.

09:39.297 --> 09:42.255
[disquieting music]

09:42.339 --> 09:45.422
♪ ♪

09:45.506 --> 09:48.506
[speaking Language of Adam]

09:55.214 --> 10:02.089
♪ ♪

10:02.172 --> 10:05.130
I know that you're awake, Ruby.

10:05.214 --> 10:08.923
♪ ♪

10:09.005 --> 10:11.089
[wings fluttering]

10:11.172 --> 10:13.756
[mysterious music]

10:13.839 --> 10:15.714
- Did I die

10:15.798 --> 10:17.756
to turn into that white woman?

10:17.839 --> 10:19.881
- No.

10:19.964 --> 10:23.756
The potion just mimics
metamorphosis.

10:23.839 --> 10:25.964
Wears off after a time.

10:26.047 --> 10:31.756
♪ ♪

10:31.839 --> 10:33.923
- Magic exists?

10:34.005 --> 10:34.964
- Does that scare you?

10:35.047 --> 10:35.964
- [shudders]

10:36.047 --> 10:40.464
♪ ♪

10:40.547 --> 10:43.464
Scared the shit outta me
to wake up white.

10:43.547 --> 10:47.089
♪ ♪

10:47.172 --> 10:50.422
Then...

10:50.506 --> 10:54.798
when I was stumbling
down the street,

10:54.881 --> 10:56.464
crazed and disheveled

10:56.547 --> 10:59.631
and screaming
at everybody around me,

10:59.714 --> 11:02.798
they weren't scared of me.

11:02.881 --> 11:05.506
They were scared for me.

11:07.381 --> 11:08.464
They all treated me like--

11:08.547 --> 11:10.255
- A human being.

11:12.798 --> 11:17.214
I know your transformation
was painful.

11:17.297 --> 11:20.464
- That wasn't pain.

11:20.547 --> 11:23.339
That was something else.

11:23.422 --> 11:24.673
Like being unmade.

11:24.756 --> 11:26.631
- I promise,
it'll be easier next time.

11:26.714 --> 11:29.506
- No, there won't be
a next time.

11:29.589 --> 11:32.255
- I have some business
to attend to.

11:34.130 --> 11:36.172
- Am I free to go?

11:36.255 --> 11:40.047
- You are free
to do whatever you please.

11:40.130 --> 11:45.381
♪ ♪

11:45.464 --> 11:47.631
[door clicks open]

11:47.714 --> 11:49.255
[door clunks shut]

11:49.339 --> 11:52.214
[foreboding music]

11:52.297 --> 11:59.339
♪ ♪

12:03.464 --> 12:06.214
- Somebody, anybody,

12:06.297 --> 12:09.214
sing a Black girl's song.

12:09.297 --> 12:12.673
Bring her out to know herself,
to know you,

12:12.756 --> 12:14.714
but sing her rhythms

12:14.798 --> 12:18.047
of caring and struggle

12:18.130 --> 12:20.214
and hard times.

12:20.297 --> 12:23.047
Sing her song of life.

12:23.130 --> 12:25.506
She's been dead so long,

12:25.589 --> 12:27.714
closed in silence so long,

12:27.798 --> 12:31.714
she doesn't know the sound
of her own voice,

12:31.798 --> 12:35.673
her infinite beauty.

12:35.756 --> 12:38.422
She's half notes,
scattered without rhythm,

12:38.506 --> 12:40.047
no tune.

12:40.130 --> 12:42.756
Sing her sighs.

12:42.839 --> 12:46.631
Sing the song
of her possibilities.

12:46.714 --> 12:48.589
Sing a righteous gospel,

12:48.673 --> 12:50.923
the making of a melody,

12:51.005 --> 12:54.214
and let her be born.

12:54.297 --> 12:56.756
Let her be born

12:56.839 --> 12:59.923
and handled warmly.

13:00.005 --> 13:02.547
I'm outside Chicago,

13:02.631 --> 13:06.255
and this is for colored girls
who have considered suicide,

13:06.339 --> 13:10.631
but are moving to the ends
of their own rainbows.

13:10.714 --> 13:13.631
[bright jazz music]

13:13.714 --> 13:19.756
♪ ♪

13:19.839 --> 13:23.881
[indistinct chatter]

13:25.923 --> 13:28.506
[door squeaks]

13:50.255 --> 13:53.673
- I did take pictures
of the pages.

13:53.756 --> 13:56.881
I just didn't have a chance
to develop them yet.

13:58.047 --> 14:01.047
- Thank you.

14:01.130 --> 14:02.881
For stopping me.

14:02.964 --> 14:05.673
[soft music]

14:05.756 --> 14:07.839
- If I wasn't there,
would you have killed him?

14:07.923 --> 14:11.297
♪ ♪

14:11.381 --> 14:13.756
- I've imagined it enough.

14:13.839 --> 14:16.339
When I was younger.

14:16.422 --> 14:18.422
Mostly after he beat me.

14:20.422 --> 14:23.506
That violence that's in him,
I thought wasn't--

14:23.589 --> 14:25.172
could never be in me.

14:25.255 --> 14:28.297
I found it in the war.

14:30.464 --> 14:32.964
- Seeing that side of you
scares me.

14:33.047 --> 14:38.839
♪ ♪

14:38.923 --> 14:41.047
- Please don't be scared of me.

14:41.130 --> 14:47.214
♪ ♪

14:47.297 --> 14:50.214
[Black Atlass'
"Return to Love"]

14:50.297 --> 14:53.214
[heartfelt guitar ballad]

14:53.297 --> 15:00.297
♪ ♪

15:12.506 --> 15:15.756
- ♪ Set that flame down,
darlin' ♪

15:15.839 --> 15:18.547
♪ ♪

15:18.631 --> 15:21.422
♪ Before you burn up ♪

15:21.506 --> 15:24.130
♪ ♪

15:24.214 --> 15:26.089
♪ Yeah, I know ♪

15:26.172 --> 15:30.464
♪ What I wanna be ♪

15:30.547 --> 15:32.547
♪ But baby, do you? ♪

15:32.631 --> 15:36.089
♪ ♪

15:36.172 --> 15:40.297
♪ Your smile can
set you free ♪

15:40.381 --> 15:42.547
♪ ♪

15:42.631 --> 15:45.756
♪ Return to love ♪

15:45.839 --> 15:48.756
♪ Return to love ♪

15:48.839 --> 15:51.631
♪ ♪

15:51.714 --> 15:56.172
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

15:56.255 --> 15:57.589
♪ Yeah ♪

15:57.673 --> 15:59.214
♪ Yeah ♪

15:59.297 --> 16:06.089
♪ ♪

16:10.756 --> 16:13.881
- ♪ You've got me in between ♪

16:13.964 --> 16:18.381
♪ The devil
and the deep blue sea ♪

16:26.089 --> 16:28.089
[sighs]

16:31.339 --> 16:33.964
Let's stop with the bullshit.

16:34.047 --> 16:37.089
I don't believe for a second
that I am special enough

16:37.172 --> 16:40.506
for you to share
your conjuring powers with.

16:40.589 --> 16:42.005
There are
a thousand colored girls

16:42.089 --> 16:43.506
on the South Side.

16:43.589 --> 16:45.464
Why share magic with me?

16:45.547 --> 16:46.714
- Why not you?

16:50.422 --> 16:53.214
[soft mysterious music]

16:53.297 --> 17:00.297
♪ ♪

17:01.756 --> 17:04.673
The first time
I laid eyes on you

17:04.756 --> 17:07.005
was the first time in a while
that I had felt magic

17:07.089 --> 17:09.005
where there was none.

17:09.089 --> 17:12.381
♪ ♪

17:12.464 --> 17:15.506
And I will need a favor
when the time comes.

17:15.589 --> 17:17.339
- What kind of favor?

17:17.422 --> 17:19.255
- There's a friend that I owe.

17:21.756 --> 17:24.464
A woman friend.

17:24.547 --> 17:25.631
Is that a problem?

17:25.714 --> 17:30.005
- Might be when I find out
what kind of favor it is.

17:30.089 --> 17:32.047
- It's small, really.

17:32.130 --> 17:33.589
Inconsequential.

17:33.673 --> 17:40.673
♪ ♪

17:43.631 --> 17:46.756
But until then,
you do as you please.

17:46.839 --> 17:49.464
Go as you please,
in whatever skin you like.

17:51.798 --> 17:54.422
I am curious.

17:54.506 --> 17:57.047
I saw the money I left
still on the nightstand.

17:57.130 --> 17:58.673
Why didn't you use any of it?

17:58.756 --> 18:00.714
- Didn't have to.

18:00.798 --> 18:04.255
I enjoyed my entire day

18:04.339 --> 18:07.172
using the only currency
that I needed:

18:07.255 --> 18:10.172
whiteness.

18:10.255 --> 18:13.756
I don't know
what is more difficult,

18:13.839 --> 18:17.130
being colored or being a woman.

18:17.214 --> 18:18.923
Most days,
I'm happy to be both,

18:19.005 --> 18:23.631
but the world keeps
interrupting,

18:23.714 --> 18:27.089
and I am sick

18:27.172 --> 18:29.714
of being interrupted.

18:29.798 --> 18:31.964
- So what's next for Ruby,

18:32.047 --> 18:34.130
uninterrupted?

18:34.214 --> 18:35.756
- ♪ Look, whoo ♪

18:35.839 --> 18:37.089
♪ I was born to flex, yes ♪

18:37.172 --> 18:38.464
♪ Diamonds on my neck ♪

18:38.547 --> 18:40.631
♪ I like boardin' jets,
I like mornin' sex ♪

18:40.714 --> 18:42.047
♪ But nothing in this world ♪

18:42.130 --> 18:43.589
♪ That I like
more than checks ♪

18:43.673 --> 18:44.631
♪ Money ♪

18:44.714 --> 18:46.047
♪ All I really wanna see
is the money ♪

18:46.130 --> 18:47.839
♪ I don't really need the D,
I need the money ♪

18:47.923 --> 18:49.964
♪ All a bad bitch need is
the money flow ♪

18:50.047 --> 18:51.047
♪ I gotta fly ♪

18:51.130 --> 18:52.297
♪ I need a jet, shit ♪

18:52.381 --> 18:53.631
♪ I need room for my legs ♪

18:53.714 --> 18:54.673
♪ I got a baby ♪
[knocks on door]

18:54.756 --> 18:55.964
♪ I need some money, yeah ♪

18:56.047 --> 18:57.422
♪ I need cheese for my egg ♪

18:57.506 --> 18:58.798
♪ All y'all bitches
in trouble ♪

18:58.881 --> 19:00.130
♪ Bring brass knuckles
to the scuffle ♪

19:00.214 --> 19:02.172
♪ I heard
that Cardi went pop, yeah ♪

19:02.255 --> 19:03.839
- Come in, Miss Davenport.

19:03.923 --> 19:05.631
- ♪ Money ♪

19:05.714 --> 19:07.506
♪ Money ♪

19:07.589 --> 19:08.506
♪ Money ♪

19:08.589 --> 19:11.089
♪ ♪

19:11.172 --> 19:13.297
- Six typing seminars.

19:13.381 --> 19:14.756
Five numbers courses.

19:14.839 --> 19:16.547
Maybe I should be worried
about you taking my job.

19:16.631 --> 19:19.172
- [chuckles]

19:19.255 --> 19:22.923
- Uh, your--your résumé,
it speaks for itself.

19:23.005 --> 19:24.631
But--
[sighs]

19:24.714 --> 19:27.464
Tell me what's not on there.

19:27.547 --> 19:29.255
Who is Hillary Davenport?

19:29.339 --> 19:31.172
[quirky music]

19:31.255 --> 19:32.798
- [laughs]

19:32.881 --> 19:36.631
I'm...an imported good.

19:36.714 --> 19:37.923
[chuckles]

19:38.005 --> 19:41.214
I grew up in a small town
in Maine and--

19:41.297 --> 19:43.172
- Really?
What town?

19:43.255 --> 19:45.339
I'm from Waterville.

19:45.422 --> 19:46.673
- Oh, it's a tiny town.

19:46.756 --> 19:48.339
You've probably never heard
of it.

19:48.422 --> 19:49.422
- Try me.

19:49.506 --> 19:53.047
- Well, we moved to Chicago
after my father died,

19:53.130 --> 19:56.506
and my mother was...

19:56.589 --> 19:59.381
an unlucky fool for love.

19:59.464 --> 20:03.005
After every breakup,
she would drag me and Leti--

20:03.089 --> 20:07.297
she would drive my sister and I
to Carson's

20:07.381 --> 20:09.464
and march us
up and down the aisles,

20:09.547 --> 20:12.255
where the salesclerk would
greet us with smiles.

20:13.589 --> 20:18.255
That was all my mother needed
to make her feel whole again.

20:18.339 --> 20:19.756
And I always dreamed of being

20:19.839 --> 20:22.047
on the other side
of the counter,

20:22.130 --> 20:24.506
to pass on that feeling

20:24.589 --> 20:27.047
to a tired, overworked mother.

20:27.130 --> 20:29.172
- How do you feel
about coloreds?

20:29.255 --> 20:30.923
[tense music]

20:31.005 --> 20:32.839
You know, working with them.

20:32.923 --> 20:34.381
- [laughing]
Oh.

20:34.464 --> 20:37.089
You're talking about
the colored gal out front?

20:38.798 --> 20:41.923
Well, if she's qualified
and hardworking,

20:42.005 --> 20:44.547
I don't see a problem with...

20:44.631 --> 20:46.381
offering her
the same opportunities

20:46.464 --> 20:48.381
us white folks take
advantage of.

20:48.464 --> 20:50.005
[quirky music]

20:50.089 --> 20:51.381
- A number of my employees quit

20:51.464 --> 20:53.589
when corporate headquarters
ended our whites-only policy.

20:53.673 --> 20:54.964
[bones cracking]
- [grunts]

20:55.047 --> 20:57.130
- Oh, but they're--
they're no race crusaders.

20:57.214 --> 20:59.589
They're just chasing
that mighty dollar.

20:59.673 --> 21:02.756
[both laugh]

21:02.839 --> 21:03.923
[bones cracking]

21:04.005 --> 21:07.255
Uh, how does...

21:07.339 --> 21:10.422
assistant manager sound to you?

21:10.506 --> 21:11.881
- Yes.
Yes!

21:11.964 --> 21:12.964
[bones crack]
[gasps]

21:13.047 --> 21:14.631
14 times over, yes.

21:14.714 --> 21:15.798
Thank you so much,

21:15.881 --> 21:17.756
but I don't wanna take up
any more of your time.

21:17.839 --> 21:18.923
- Oh, don't be silly.

21:19.005 --> 21:21.547
It's my job to make sure
everyone feels right at home.

21:21.631 --> 21:22.839
- [grunts]

21:22.923 --> 21:25.047
- Welcome to
the Marshall Field's family.

21:25.130 --> 21:26.089
[chuckles]

21:26.172 --> 21:28.089
Uh, shall we take a tour
of the store?

21:28.172 --> 21:30.130
- But first, the ladies' room.

21:30.214 --> 21:32.297
- Uh, Miss Davenport,

21:32.381 --> 21:36.422
you dropped your, uh...

21:36.506 --> 21:37.631
perfume?

21:37.714 --> 21:38.964
- [grunting]

21:39.047 --> 21:40.964
[bones cracking]

21:41.047 --> 21:43.172
[squelching]

21:43.255 --> 21:46.422
[suspenseful music]

21:46.506 --> 21:48.089
♪ ♪

21:48.172 --> 21:51.297
[elevator ringing]

21:51.381 --> 21:52.464
[bones crack]
[grunts]

21:52.547 --> 21:53.631
[door clunks]

21:53.714 --> 21:57.047
[moaning]

21:59.172 --> 22:02.172
[whines]
[squelching]

22:05.547 --> 22:07.089
[bones crack]

22:10.881 --> 22:12.673
[distant shouting]

22:12.756 --> 22:15.964
[distant baby crying]

22:16.047 --> 22:17.464
[keys jingle]

22:17.547 --> 22:19.506
[lock clicks]

22:29.547 --> 22:32.464
- Was it the ofays
or the niggers this time?

22:37.047 --> 22:40.005
[Frank Ocean's "Bad Religion"]

22:40.089 --> 22:43.047
[melancholy organ music]

22:43.130 --> 22:48.506
♪ ♪

22:48.589 --> 22:51.506
- ♪ Taxi driver ♪

22:51.589 --> 22:53.964
♪ Be my shrink for the hour ♪

22:54.047 --> 22:55.964
♪ Leave the meter running ♪

22:56.047 --> 22:58.214
♪ ♪

22:58.297 --> 23:01.172
- [grunts]
- ♪ You said "Allahu Akbar" ♪

23:01.255 --> 23:03.714
♪ I told him
"Don't curse me" ♪

23:03.798 --> 23:04.714
- [moaning]

23:04.798 --> 23:07.130
- ♪ "Bo Bo, you need prayer" ♪

23:07.214 --> 23:10.964
♪ I guess
it couldn't hurt me ♪

23:11.047 --> 23:15.381
♪ If it brings me
to my knees ♪

23:15.464 --> 23:19.047
♪ It's a bad religion ♪

23:19.130 --> 23:20.756
♪ Oh ♪

23:20.839 --> 23:23.214
♪ Unrequited love ♪

23:23.297 --> 23:24.547
[both grunting]

23:24.631 --> 23:26.255
♪ To me, it's nothing ♪

23:26.339 --> 23:30.089
♪ But a one-man cult ♪

23:30.172 --> 23:31.881
♪ And cyanide ♪

23:31.964 --> 23:35.714
♪ In my Styrofoam cup ♪

23:35.798 --> 23:39.005
♪ I can never make him
love me ♪

23:39.089 --> 23:41.464
♪ Never make him love me ♪

23:41.547 --> 23:42.881
♪ No ♪

23:42.964 --> 23:45.047
♪ No, oh ♪

23:45.130 --> 23:49.130
♪ It's a,
it's a bad religion ♪

23:49.214 --> 23:51.547
♪ To be in love with someone ♪

23:51.631 --> 23:54.923
♪ Who could never love you ♪

23:55.005 --> 23:57.255
♪ Oh, oh, only bad ♪

23:57.339 --> 24:01.714
♪ Only bad religion ♪

24:01.798 --> 24:03.464
♪ Could have me feeling ♪

24:03.547 --> 24:05.881
♪ The way I do ♪

24:05.964 --> 24:08.381
♪ ♪

24:08.464 --> 24:09.381
- [moans]

24:09.464 --> 24:12.381
[refined piano music]

24:12.464 --> 24:19.130
♪ ♪

24:22.506 --> 24:24.923
- Miss Davenport,
you look beautiful.

24:25.005 --> 24:26.255
- [chuckles]

24:26.339 --> 24:30.464
♪ ♪

24:30.547 --> 24:32.506
- My lips may not be
the Blarney Stone,

24:32.589 --> 24:34.964
but here's hoping
good luck rubs off on you

24:35.047 --> 24:36.297
your first day.

24:36.381 --> 24:43.381
♪ ♪

24:45.214 --> 24:46.506
- And where is she?

24:46.589 --> 24:48.005
Made me wait.

24:48.089 --> 24:50.464
12 minutes now,
I've been standing here.

24:50.547 --> 24:51.798
Where's the perfume girl?

24:51.881 --> 24:54.714
The service here is...

24:54.798 --> 24:58.297
- It's awful.
- I'm finished with her.

24:58.381 --> 25:00.422
- You can't uplift
the lives of our customers

25:00.506 --> 25:02.339
if you're not
at your counter, Tamara.

25:02.422 --> 25:03.839
- So sorry, Miss Davenport.

25:03.923 --> 25:05.756
Was only supposed to be gone
a couple of minutes.

25:05.839 --> 25:07.130
Madge needed
some shoes re-shelved,

25:07.214 --> 25:09.339
but then Barb needed
her dressing rooms wiped down.

25:09.422 --> 25:10.547
And Cathy--
- Tamara?

25:10.631 --> 25:11.714
- Yes, ma'am.

25:11.798 --> 25:13.172
- Exhale.

25:13.255 --> 25:15.005
You're not in any trouble.

25:15.089 --> 25:19.506
I just...like to get to know
all of my employees.

25:19.589 --> 25:23.339
I remember you saying
you applied on a whim.

25:23.422 --> 25:26.089
- I'm sorry.
Did I say that to you?

25:27.631 --> 25:30.214
- Mr. Hughes must have
mentioned it.

25:30.297 --> 25:31.798
[laughs]

25:31.881 --> 25:35.506
He also told me
that your hiring caused...

25:35.589 --> 25:38.839
quite a stir.

25:38.923 --> 25:39.881
I hope you're still feeling

25:39.964 --> 25:43.506
a part
of the Marshall Field's family.

25:43.589 --> 25:46.047
- I am, ma'am.

25:48.881 --> 25:52.839
- And j-just remember,
no matter what anybody says,

25:52.923 --> 25:54.923
they can't take
your educational achievements

25:55.005 --> 25:56.589
away from you.

25:56.673 --> 25:58.255
- I wouldn't call
a seventh grade education

25:58.339 --> 26:00.381
much of an achievement.

26:00.464 --> 26:02.005
- You didn't graduate
from high school?

26:02.089 --> 26:05.381
♪ ♪

26:05.464 --> 26:07.506
So you took
some accounting courses

26:07.589 --> 26:09.714
down at
the Frederick Douglass Center?

26:09.798 --> 26:11.798
- I didn't even know
they had those there.

26:13.673 --> 26:14.673
- Hmm.

26:16.464 --> 26:18.089
Mm.

26:20.673 --> 26:23.172
Your hands are a bit ashy.

26:23.255 --> 26:26.381
- ♪ Please give your love
to me ♪

26:26.464 --> 26:27.881
[laughter]

26:27.964 --> 26:29.047
- For how hard we work,

26:29.130 --> 26:31.255
they should give all this to us
for free.

26:31.339 --> 26:32.964
- Madge, you look
like Marilyn Monroe

26:33.047 --> 26:35.172
in "How to Marry
a Millionaire."

26:35.255 --> 26:38.547
- Barb, which way
is the wind blowing?

26:38.631 --> 26:39.589
- That coat would close

26:39.673 --> 26:41.547
if you stopped stuffing
your face with bonbons.

26:41.631 --> 26:43.255
[laughter]

26:43.339 --> 26:44.923
- All right,
it's been 30 minutes.

26:45.005 --> 26:47.047
We really should get back
on the floor.

26:47.130 --> 26:49.589
- Well, Hillary,
you're the boss.

26:49.673 --> 26:51.964
So we can either head
back out there

26:52.047 --> 26:54.130
to the salt mines, or...

26:54.214 --> 26:57.464
- You can try on
these naughty stilettos

26:57.547 --> 27:01.381
and live a fuckin' little.

27:01.464 --> 27:02.923
- Come on.

27:03.005 --> 27:04.130
- Mm.

27:04.214 --> 27:06.422
[both laugh]

27:06.506 --> 27:09.631
- Oh, speaking of--of bosses,
has...

27:09.714 --> 27:13.339
has Paul ever...gotten fresh
with any of you?

27:13.422 --> 27:16.798
♪ ♪

27:16.881 --> 27:19.881
[laughter]

27:21.673 --> 27:23.631
- Paul, "I live
in a Norman Rockwell painting

27:23.714 --> 27:25.964
with my wife and two kids,"
getting fresh?

27:26.047 --> 27:27.673
[laughing]
No way.

27:27.756 --> 27:29.506
- Like my father always says,

27:29.589 --> 27:30.964
"Boy, is paranoia the price

27:31.047 --> 27:32.798
of being a working girl
in America."

27:32.881 --> 27:34.255
[radio tunes]

27:34.339 --> 27:36.464
- Hillary, let's see you strut!

27:36.547 --> 27:38.172
[laughter]
- ♪ All rooty ♪

27:38.255 --> 27:41.297
♪ Tutti frutti, all rooty ♪

27:41.381 --> 27:42.506
- Wowee!

27:42.589 --> 27:43.964
- Oh, cut a rug!

27:44.047 --> 27:46.297
[both laugh]

27:46.381 --> 27:48.589
- ♪ A-wop bop-a-loo-bop,
a-lop-bop-bop ♪

27:48.673 --> 27:51.756
- You should sign up
for Herb Mintz's show.

27:51.839 --> 27:53.506
- With the rhythm
in those hips,

27:53.589 --> 27:55.464
she's ready
for the colored version.

27:55.547 --> 27:57.297
[laughter]

27:57.381 --> 28:00.172
- Okay, can I just say
what we've all been thinking?

28:00.255 --> 28:02.172
I hope we don't see
any more Tamaras

28:02.255 --> 28:03.339
coming through the front door.

28:03.422 --> 28:04.673
- Well, if there are,

28:04.756 --> 28:07.005
let's hope they're
more qualified than her.

28:07.089 --> 28:09.214
- Course she's unqualified.
She's a Negro.

28:09.297 --> 28:10.964
- Barb!

28:11.047 --> 28:12.214
- What?

28:12.297 --> 28:16.673
I was polite enough not to use
the less civilized word.

28:16.756 --> 28:19.005
- Hillary, you were
with Tamara earlier.

28:19.089 --> 28:21.381
You seem comfortable with her.

28:21.464 --> 28:24.839
- I was giving her work advice.

28:24.923 --> 28:26.047
- You think
you can convince her

28:26.130 --> 28:29.214
to take us to a bar
on the South Side?

28:29.297 --> 28:31.881
It'll be like a safari.

28:31.964 --> 28:34.130
And we need a guide.

28:34.214 --> 28:35.172
- Why would you want
to go there?

28:35.255 --> 28:37.214
There's nothing special
about the South Side,

28:37.297 --> 28:38.923
trust me, I know.

28:39.005 --> 28:40.673
- Oh, my God.
- You've been there?

28:40.756 --> 28:42.422
- Were you scared
being around all of those--

28:42.506 --> 28:43.714
- People?

28:43.798 --> 28:45.673
- ♪ Tutti frutti, all rooty ♪

28:45.756 --> 28:47.381
[laughter]
- We're going.

28:47.464 --> 28:48.547
- Ooh.
- Oh, yes!

28:48.631 --> 28:51.005
- ♪ A-wop, bop-a-loo-bop,
a-lop-bam-boom ♪

28:51.089 --> 28:54.089
[bells ringing]

29:04.422 --> 29:06.464
[The Charms'
"My Baby Dearest Darling"]

29:06.547 --> 29:08.255
- What a hunk of man.

29:08.339 --> 29:10.589
[romantic doo-wop music]

29:10.673 --> 29:12.881
- ♪ My baby dearest darling ♪

29:12.964 --> 29:14.756
- He's with you?

29:14.839 --> 29:16.589
- Only when he behaves.

29:16.673 --> 29:20.547
- ♪ My baby dearest darling ♪

29:20.631 --> 29:22.130
♪ I love you so ♪

29:22.214 --> 29:24.756
- ♪ All my love deep inside ♪

29:24.839 --> 29:27.089
♪ ♪

29:27.172 --> 29:28.255
- Night-night, ladies.

29:28.339 --> 29:31.923
- ♪ I can't hide ♪

29:32.005 --> 29:34.923
- He's so--oh.

29:35.005 --> 29:37.089
- Can't just be
showing up here.

29:37.172 --> 29:39.089
- It doesn't look
like I embarrassed you.

29:39.172 --> 29:41.172
- [chuckles]

29:43.214 --> 29:44.297
- How was the first day

29:44.381 --> 29:48.255
of your dream job,
Miss Davenport?

29:48.339 --> 29:51.547
- Well, it's better than being
someone's damn charwoman.

29:51.631 --> 29:53.422
Hmm.

29:53.506 --> 29:55.881
- You don't want me to kiss you
as Hillary.

29:55.964 --> 29:58.798
- Do you want to kiss Hillary?

29:58.881 --> 30:01.464
- I wanna kiss...

30:01.547 --> 30:03.589
whatever you want me to kiss.

30:07.339 --> 30:09.589
- Hmm.

30:09.673 --> 30:11.756
- Hold off on that.

30:11.839 --> 30:13.798
[mysterious music]

30:13.881 --> 30:16.756
I'm gonna need that favor.

30:16.839 --> 30:19.756
Tonight.

30:19.839 --> 30:21.005
- Finally,

30:21.089 --> 30:23.547
the devil tells me
what deal I've made with him.

30:24.839 --> 30:26.381
- I need you to attend a party.

30:28.089 --> 30:29.839
Miss Braithwhite

30:29.923 --> 30:32.506
will give you the rest
of the details when you arrive.

30:32.589 --> 30:34.589
♪ ♪

30:34.673 --> 30:36.422
- [grunts]

30:36.506 --> 30:40.172
♪ ♪

30:40.255 --> 30:42.964
- There's a box
in the back seat.

30:43.047 --> 30:45.798
It's got your name all over.

30:45.881 --> 30:51.172
♪ ♪

30:51.255 --> 30:53.047
- Mm.

30:53.130 --> 31:00.089
♪ ♪

31:03.381 --> 31:04.673
- They were up north,
is that correct?

31:04.756 --> 31:05.756
- Oh, right, right, right.

31:05.839 --> 31:07.005
- You could view
the captain's accomplishments

31:07.089 --> 31:08.172
as a way to immortality.

31:08.255 --> 31:10.964
- We suffered a major loss
in the Ardham incident,

31:11.047 --> 31:12.339
but initiation must
remain exclusive.

31:12.422 --> 31:14.214
- Perhaps he's recovered
Horatio's stolen pages.

31:14.297 --> 31:16.297
- It was a unanimous decision
by the members

31:16.381 --> 31:19.339
that I take the reins
of our social club.

31:19.422 --> 31:21.172
- What of the rumors
of defection

31:21.255 --> 31:23.881
following Hiram's death?

31:23.964 --> 31:27.089
- Mr. Lowe was
certainly unexpected.

31:27.172 --> 31:29.714
- There were some
that abandoned us,

31:29.798 --> 31:31.381
but look around.

31:31.464 --> 31:33.923
It's only made
our brotherhood stronger.

31:35.297 --> 31:36.381
[door clacks]

31:36.464 --> 31:38.339
- The fuck is that bitch?

31:38.422 --> 31:41.422
[dishes clattering]

31:43.255 --> 31:46.172
[foreboding music]

31:46.255 --> 31:53.255
♪ ♪

31:55.464 --> 31:58.756
You were supposed to be here
an hour ago.

31:58.839 --> 32:01.923
- William does like
a demanding woman.

32:04.005 --> 32:05.923
- What you need me to do here?

32:06.005 --> 32:08.089
- Simple, really.

32:08.172 --> 32:11.214
Just, uh, hide this
in the police captain's office.

32:11.297 --> 32:12.297
- Captain?

32:12.381 --> 32:13.297
[scoffs]

32:13.381 --> 32:15.422
William didn't say anything
about no cops.

32:15.506 --> 32:16.589
You trying to get me killed.

32:16.673 --> 32:18.172
- Ruby.

32:20.547 --> 32:22.673
Do you care for him at all?

32:24.339 --> 32:26.839
Beyond the opportunity
he's providing you?

32:29.673 --> 32:32.589
William is the rightful heir
to this lodge.

32:32.673 --> 32:35.589
The captain tried to kill him
to take his seat.

32:35.673 --> 32:36.798
Shot him in the back

32:36.881 --> 32:38.339
and dumped his body
in the river

32:38.422 --> 32:40.964
like he was a piece of trash.

32:41.047 --> 32:44.881
♪ ♪

32:44.964 --> 32:48.422
Lancaster believes
that he succeeded.

32:48.506 --> 32:50.923
But William survived
with my help...

32:52.881 --> 32:55.839
And with yours,
he'll have his revenge.

32:55.923 --> 33:02.881
♪ ♪

33:09.005 --> 33:11.923
[intense music]

33:12.005 --> 33:19.005
♪ ♪

33:22.756 --> 33:25.005
- What?

33:27.214 --> 33:28.881
[gasps]

33:28.964 --> 33:32.172
[screaming]

33:32.255 --> 33:35.381
♪ ♪

33:35.464 --> 33:36.589
[gasps]

33:36.673 --> 33:38.839
[breathing heavily]

33:38.923 --> 33:41.005
- You okay?

33:41.089 --> 33:42.673
- How long was I out?

33:42.756 --> 33:44.839
- [sighs]
Not long.

33:44.923 --> 33:48.172
I let you sleep.

33:48.255 --> 33:50.422
You've been going nonstop.

33:56.923 --> 33:57.839
This looks like

33:57.923 --> 34:00.005
the "Little Orphan Annie"
radio puzzles

34:00.089 --> 34:01.756
I used to play with
when I was younger.

34:03.964 --> 34:07.506
I'm guessing
it's a little more complicated.

34:07.589 --> 34:11.714
- Well, I figured I'd start
with what's in my arsenal.

34:11.797 --> 34:15.547
These are my initials
